  "prompt": "What do if I forget my user id and password of forex card HDFC?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten the user ID and password for your HDFC Forex Card, you can follow these steps to recover or reset your credentials:\n\n### **1. Visit the Official HDFC Bank Website**\n- Navigate to the [HDFC Bank Forex Card Services](https://www.hdfcbank.com/) official website.\n\n### **2. Locate the Login Page**\n- On the homepage, find the login section related to Forex Card services. This might be under sections like \"Cards\" or \"Forex Services.\"\n\n### **3. Use the 'Forgot User ID' or 'Forgot Password' Option**\n- Click on the **\"Forgot User ID\"** or **\"Forgot Password\"** link typically found below the login fields.\n\n### **4. Provide Required Details**\n- **For User ID Recovery:**\n  - You may need to enter details such as your registered email address, mobile number, or the Forex Card number.\n- **For Password Reset:**\n  - After retrieving your User ID, follow the prompts to reset your password. This might involve answering security questions or receiving a verification code via SMS or email.\n\n### **5. Verify Your Identity**\n- Complete any verification steps as prompted to ensure the security of your account.\n\n### **6. Contact HDFC Customer Support (If Needed)**\nIf you're unable to recover your User ID or reset your password online, consider the following options:\n- **Call Customer Care:** Reach out to HDFC Bank's customer support at **1800 267 6161** (for callers within India) or the appropriate international number if you're abroad.\n- **Visit a Branch:** Go to the nearest HDFC Bank branch with your Forex Card and valid identification documents to get assistance in person.\n- **Email Support:** You can also send an email detailing your issue to HDFC's customer support email address, which can be found on their official website.\n\n### **7. Secure Your Account**\n- Once you've regained access, consider updating your password to something memorable yet secure.\n- Ensure your contact details (like email and mobile number) are up-to-date to facilitate easier recovery in the future.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n- **Keep Your Information Handy:** Always remember to keep a record of your Forex Card details and associated online account information in a secure place.\n- **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (If Available):** This adds an extra layer of security to your account.\n\nIf you continue to face issues, it's best to get in touch directly with HDFC Bank's customer support to receive personalized assistance.",
